

Class Declaration
================

You can define a class in javascript using class keyword

class Person {
    constructor(name, age) {
        this.name = name;
        this.age = age;
    }

    great() {
        console.log(`Hello, my name is ${this.name} and I am ${this.age} years old`);
    }
}

const person1 = new Person("Alice", 30);
person1.great(); //